                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2697</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Lithuanian National Council</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: The Department has received your
                    communication of November 14 and has the honor to inform you that the points
                    which are raised in the communication relative to the aspirations for Lithuanian
                    independence have been carefully noted and will receive due consideration in
                    connection with similar questions which will require attention in negotiations
                    for a general peace which will prove lasting.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
